uébec (Canada) -- tDiscovering haitian youth’s spiritual epistemology through a culturally based summer program in florida -- tLes écoliers haïtiens à montréal -- tSexual experiences among haitian american adolescents in miami dade, florida -- tNotices Biographiques -- tEnglish Index -- tIndex Français0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aLe présent ouvrage examine les contextes dans lesquels les jeunes Haïtiens et les jeunes descendants d’Haïtiens négocient leurs conditions socioculturelles en Haïti et dans différentes sociétés des Amériques. Il embrasse une perspective transdisciplinaire à travers des thématiques croisées, traitées dans un cadre théorique axé autour des concepts de pratique, de génération, d’identité et de circulation transnationale. Les chapitres sont élaborés à partir des recherches longitudinales ainsi que des études de cas ou des situations cliniques recueillies dans différents contextes socioculturels. Ce livre apporte un éclairage unique sur la complexité des processus identitaires, sur l’ambivalence des modes d’appartenance et d’engagements des jeunes en Haïti, dans et à travers les sociétés dans lesquelles ils vivent ou circulent, et vers Haïti à partir de leurs sociétés d’accueil dans les Amériques. This book examines the contexts in which Haitian youth and young people of Haitian descent negotiate their socio-cultural conditions in Haiti and in different societies across the Americas. It uses a transdisciplinary perspective to consider interconnected themes affecting these youth through a theoretical framework centered on the concepts of practice, generation, identity and transnational circulation. The chapters are developed from longitudinal research as well as case studies or clinical situations collected in different socio-cultural contexts. This book provides unique insights into the complexity of identity processes as well as the ambivalence of the modes of belonging and engagement of young people of Haitian descent in Haiti and the societies throughout the Americas in which they live or circulate.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aHaitianszAmericaxSocial conditions. 0aImmigrant youthzAmericaxSocial conditions. 0aYouthzHaitixSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / General.2bisacsh1 aAlix, Lourdes Stéphane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBernard, Léonel, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBernard, Léonel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCela, Toni, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aCela, Toni, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCela, Toni, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCharlène, Désir, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCélestin, Michel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDorvil, Henri, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aDorvil, Henri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDorvil, Henri, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDésir, Charlène, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aDésir, Charlène, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGallagher, Suzanne, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aGallagher, Suzanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHall, Pamela, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHall, Pamela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJoseph, Handerson, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aJoseph, Handerson, econtr